{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "In May, properties on Long Island will be up for auction at prices between 20 percent and 30 percent of their prestorm values.", "abstract": "The Appraisal column; New York State will auction 150 properties in Long Island that were destroyed by Hurricane Sandy in 2012 at prices between 20 percent and 30 percent of their prestorm values; buyers will have three years to either elevate homes out of flood range or demolish them and build homes that will withstand rising tides and fierce storms.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "23", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "V", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Matt", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "A."}], "original": "By MATT A.V. CHABAN"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/17/nyregion/battered-by-hurricane-sandy-bought-by-new-york-and-for-sale-for-a-song.html", "lead_paragraph": "In May, properties on Long Island will be up for auction at prices between 20 percent and 30 percent of their prestorm values.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Battered by Hurricane, Bought by the State and for Sale for a Song", "main": "Battered by Hurricane Sandy, Bought by New York and for Sale for a Song", "content_kicker": "The Appraisal", "kicker": "The Appraisal"}, "_id": "55069ba938f0d85e90e001ed", "word_count": "1073", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/03/16/nyregion/16APPRAISAL-Y/16APPRAISAL-Y-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/03/16/nyregion/16APPRAISAL-Y/16APPRAISAL-Y-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2015/03/16/nyregion/16APPRAISAL-Y/16APPRAISAL-Y-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/03/16/nyregion/16APPRAISAL-Y/16APPRAISAL-Y-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/03/1